Atomic Traceless Quadrupole Moment Tensors:
------------------------------------------
  Q(A) = Traceless Form of Quadrupole Moment Tensor of Atom A's Electronic Charge
         Density Distribution, Using the Nucleus of Atom A as Origin
  Q_XX(A) = -[3<Rho*x*x>(A) - <Rho*r*r>(A)]
  Q_XY(A) = -3<Rho*x*y>(A)
  Q_XZ(A) = -3<Rho*x*z>(A)
  Q_YY(A) = -[3<Rho*y*y>(A) - <Rho*r*r>(A)]
  Q_YZ(A) = -3<Rho*y*z>(A)
  Q_ZZ(A) = -[3<Rho*z*z>(A) - <Rho*r*r>(A)]
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
